data.title: Through the facilitation of COMSTECH, our delegation visited the Islamabad office of Muslim Hands. The delegation includes Health CECM...
data.meta_description:
10 likes, 0 comments - health.mombasa on November 2, 2023: "Through the facilitation of COMSTECH, our delegation visited the Islamabad office of Muslim Hands. 

The delegation includes Health CECM Dr. Swabah Ahmed Omar as team leader, Salma Noor, the Focal Person for COMSTECH, and Abdallah Daleno, Chief Officer Public Health and Disease Prevention.

During the visit, the delegation had a comprehensive meeting with Arsalan Nusrat, Director of the Global Operations Development Department at Muslim Hands UK; Syed Javid Gillani, Executive Director of Muslim Hands Pakistan; and Rehan Tahir, Manager of Communication and Public Relations at Muslim Hands Pakistan.

The meeting focused on discussing significant initiatives related to Health, Education, and Clean Water projects in Mombasa County, with the support of Muslim Hands.

COMSTECH's mission is to empower Muslim-majority countries in the fields of Science and Technology, Higher Education, and the Health Sector. 

The initiatives discussed in this meeting align with this mission, underscoring the organization's commitment to supporting Muslim-majority Countries including Mombasa County.".
